---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How much time does this require?",
    answer: "Our system is designed for busy women. Expect 3-5 hours per week for training, plus the time you already spend eating. No rigid meal plans. Weekly check-ins take 5-10 minutes, and bi-weekly review or live coaching calls are scheduled around your calendar."
  },
  {
    question: "What's included in the bloodwork analysis?",
    answer: "We analyze 55 biomarkers across hormonal health (LH, FSH, AMH, DHEA, SHBG, testosterone, thyroid, cortisol), metabolic function (glucose, insulin, HbA1c), cardiovascular markers (ApoB, Lp(a), LDL-P), inflammation indicators, micronutrient status, and recovery/aging markers. Your labs become the blueprint for every protocol decision."
  },
  {
    question: "How do you address women's hormonal health?",
    answer: "Women's hormonal optimization requires a different lens. We analyze a full female hormone panel: LH, FSH, AMH, DHEA-S, SHBG, and testosterone, alongside a complete thyroid panel and cortisol. Whether you're navigating perimenopause, menopause, or simply want to understand what's shifting, protocols are tailored to your life stage. Everything is data-driven."
  },
  {
    question: "Will I have to do intense workouts?",
    answer: "Your training is built around your recovery data, your schedule, and your goals. Sessions are 30-45 minutes. No junk volume, no hours in the gym. If you're recovering from a stressful week, your programming adjusts. The goal is to get stronger and more resilient without burning you out."
  },
  {
    question: "Is this just another fitness program?",
    answer: "No. This is full-stack health optimization. Unlike programs that give you a workout PDF, we integrate biomarker data, nutrition architecture, training protocols, sleep/recovery optimization, and ongoing coaching into one connected system. Every variable is linked. Nothing is siloed."
  },
  {
    question: "What if I travel frequently for work?",
    answer: "Our system was designed for women with demanding schedules. You'll receive specific recommendations for hotel gyms, restaurant menus, and on-the-go nutrition strategies. Your training adapts based on what equipment is available, and our coaching team is available to adjust protocols in real-time."
  },
  {
    question: "How is this different from other wellness programs?",
    answer: "Most solutions are fragmented. Your doctor doesn't talk to your trainer. Your nutritionist doesn't see your labs. We integrate everything: your labs dictate your training, your training informs your nutrition, your recovery data adjusts your programming. One connected system with one team coordinating your transformation."
  },
  {
    question: "Will lifting weights make me bulky?",
    answer: "No. Women don't produce enough testosterone to build bulk the way men do. What strength training will do is increase your bone density, improve your metabolic rate, change your body composition, and make you feel strong. The women in our program lose inches, fit into clothes they haven't worn in years, and look leaner. Not one has ever said they got too bulky."
  },
  {
    question: "Do I have to give up wine and chocolate?",
    answer: "Your wine and your chocolate are safe. We're not here to take away the things you enjoy. We're here to help you understand how they fit into your overall picture. You might learn that a glass of wine on Tuesday affects your Wednesday recovery score, and then you get to decide what to do with that information. Knowledge, not restriction."
  },
  {
    question: "What about holidays and vacations?",
    answer: "You live your life. Fully. Holidays, birthdays, beach trips, girls' weekends. We give you simple frameworks so you can enjoy yourself without spiraling. The system is built to flex with real life."
  },
  {
    question: "Can my partner do this too?",
    answer: "Yes. We coach several couples and it's one of the most effective setups we see. You're in the same kitchen, same schedule, same life. Having a partner on the same system creates natural accountability without either of you having to be the enforcer. We tailor protocols individually, but the shared commitment makes a real difference."
  },
  {
    question: "How much does this cost?",
    answer: "Pricing is custom because every client's situation is different. What we can tell you: most clients invest less per month than a single specialist visit, and flexible payment options are available. We walk through everything on your consult. No pressure, no surprises."
  },
  {
    question: "What if it doesn't work for me?",
    answer: "We offer a 30-day satisfaction guarantee. Complete your onboarding, follow the protocols, submit your check-ins, and log your training and nutrition. If after 30 days you're not satisfied, we'll refund your coaching investment. Lab fees and supplements are non-refundable once ordered, but the coaching itself is fully backed. We can do this because the system works when you show up for it."
  }
];
---

<section id="faq" class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-card/50 relative overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Subtle background glow -->
  <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-primary/5 rounded-full blur-[60px]"></div>
  <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-[300px] h-[300px] bg-primary/5 rounded-full blur-[60px]"></div>

  <div class="container px-4 relative z-10">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1.5fr] gap-12 lg:gap-16 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Left column: sticky header -->
      <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-24 lg:self-start">
        <span class="text-primary text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4 block">
          FAQ
        </span>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
          Questions We<br />
          <span class="text-gradient">Hear Often</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-8">
          Everything you need to know before getting started. If your question is not covered here, book a consult and we will walk through it together.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right column: accordion -->
      <div class="space-y-3">
        {faqs.map((faq, index) => (
          <div
            class="faq-item group rounded-xl border border-border bg-background hover:border-primary/30 hover:shadow-[0_0_20px_hsl(var(--primary)/0.1)] transition-all duration-200 overflow-hidden"
            data-index={index}
          >
            <button
              class="faq-trigger w-full text-left py-5 px-5 sm:px-6 flex items-center justify-between font-medium"
              aria-expanded="false"
            >
              <span class="text-foreground group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">{faq.question}</span>
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="faq-chevron transition-transform duration-200 flex-shrink-0 ml-4 text-muted-foreground"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-content hidden px-5 sm:px-6 pb-5">
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base">{faq.answer}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-trigger').forEach(trigger => {
    trigger.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const item = trigger.closest('.faq-item');
      const content = item?.querySelector('.faq-content');
      const chevron = item?.querySelector('.faq-chevron');
      const isOpen = trigger.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';

      // Close all others
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(other => {
        if (other !== item) {
          other.querySelector('.faq-trigger')?.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          other.querySelector('.faq-content')?.classList.add('hidden');
          other.querySelector('.faq-chevron')?.classList.remove('rotate-180');
          other.classList.remove('border-primary/40', 'shadow-[0_0_20px_hsl(var(--primary)/0.08)]');
        }
      });

      // Toggle current
      trigger.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!isOpen));
      content?.classList.toggle('hidden');
      chevron?.classList.toggle('rotate-180');
      if (!isOpen) {
        item?.classList.add('border-primary/40', 'shadow-[0_0_20px_hsl(var(--primary)/0.08)]');
      } else {
        item?.classList.remove('border-primary/40', 'shadow-[0_0_20px_hsl(var(--primary)/0.08)]');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
